post_text: Last evening, the Leavenworth Board of Education met in Special Session to receive an update on the Pioneer Restart Plan, and to review the Leavenworth County Health Department's gating criteria and guidance for reopening schools. The Board voted 6-0 to accept the gating criteria as presented (attached) with two consecutive weeks of status change utilized to determine a shift in operational status from green to yellow to red phase considerations. Leavenworth County is currently in the yellow phase in three criteria of: 1) community testing positive percentage, 2) total cases per 100,000; and 3) daily case average. This information will be posted each Tuesday on the district's web site: … More

August 24 at 3:12 PM ·

It looks a little different this year...but, we are PIONEERS... and, we are back in school! It is so awesome to have our students back in the halls of this amazing school. It's been a GREAT day at LHS!

Pictured: students checking in this morning, getting the lay of the land in class, having a socially distanced lunch, and a biggie - our first AVID senior, Addison, is using his AVID study skills to take a college test today!

First day of school = huge success!

post_text:
Pioneer Restart - Welcome Back Message

Our school leadership team took a brief “mask break” this week to provide a general overview to families and students in advance of the official beginning of the 20-21 academic year.

https://youtu.be/5i7MHxAo5Kw

Please look directly to your child’s school for specific information about individual building protocols for next week’s In-Person schedule, as well as communication for those students enrolled in Rigorous Remote or Leavenworth Virtual School for the first semester.

The Leavenworth Unified School District thanks our school community for their continued support of our staff and administrators, as we work hard to reconnect with students as safely as possible.

shared_text:
Leavenworth Senior High School
May 18 at 8:05 AM ·

Congratulations to Sam Casmus and Sisi Wang on being accepted to the Dole Youth Civic Leadership Institute this coming July. This is quite an honor as only 50 students from across the state of Kansas are accepted to attend. Though this year's session will be virtual, we are certain they will both learn a great deal.

The Dole Youth Civic Leadership Institute is a leadership opportunity held at the Dole Institute of Politics at the University of Kansas. It focuses on the importance of civic engagement in our democracy through a variety of speakers, workshops, and brainstorming sessions.

Again, congratulations - LHS is proud of you!

USD 453 updates: There will be no Continuous Learning, or Child Nutrition services (breakfast/lunch) on Friday, April 10. However, as there is no longer a scheduled district PD day for Monday, we WILL have planned teacher/student instructional activities for Monday, April 13. Please check directly with your child's teacher or school for assigned work.

Additionally, beginning on Monday, the Child Nutrition Department will expand our free breakfast/lunch service (for children ages 1-18) to include three remote service locations of 20-minute windows per the following sites: Woodland Village (10:20 - 10:40 a.m.); west side of 10th avenue across from Pin Oaks apartments (10:50 - 11:10 a.m.); and Earl Lawson - upper parking lot (11:30 - 11:50 a.m.). See flyer image for details.

Please join us in thanking our dedicated Child Nutrition staff for working hard to find ways to continue to serve meals to Leavenworth students.

Leavenworth County Health Department
March 28 at 8:00 AM ·

Making sure you're well-stocked on the essentials is smart with uncertainty about how COVID-19 social distancing recommendations could affect your daily routine and your family's needs. Regardless of how COVID-19 spreads, however, Leavenworth County will NOT order the closure of grocery stores or pharmacies.
So, buy what you need to provide for your family for up to two weeks for general preparedness. But there's no need to stock up for any more than that. A little consideration for our neighbors is going to go a long way as we get through this together. #KansasStrong

post_text:
Thank you for all the kind and supportive notes, and offers to provide assistance, from throughout our school community this week. Our staff is working hard to make plans for Kansas State Department of Education Continuous Learning launching next week, and find news ways to stay connected with students for the remainder of the 2019-20 academic year.

Leavenworth USD 453 has incredibly dedicated staff members, and they sincerely miss seeing our kiddos on a daily basis. As proof of the creativity, passion for learning, and call to service from throughout the school district, meet Earl Lawson Elementary 's music teacher, Ms. Jordan Ward.

The rest of this school year might look entirely different than any other, but Pioneers were made for moments like these...and we will persevere together.

https://youtu.be/q5j_2eJ3ZQQ

Leavenworth Public Schools Education Foundation
March 17 at 2:07 PM ·

It is with sadness and regret that we must announce the CANCELLATION of the 19th Annual LV Education Foundation Breakfast. Due to all of the health and safety issues surrounding our community, it is just not the time to have such a large gathering, no matter how celebratory in nature.

On behalf of the LV Education Foundation, we thank you again for your amazing giving this year! Thank you for serving as such strong partners for our Leavenworth children - for making great things happen in our schools!

We will not be rescheduling the event, as there are just too many moving parts, and uncertain times ahead.

Be safe out there...and, THANK YOU for your most generous giving!

JROTC Raiders Meet With US Army Combined Arms Center and Fort Leavenworth Commanding General

This week the Leavenworth High School JROTC Raiders team was invited to a reception at the home of Combined Arms Center and Fort Leavenworth Commanding General Lt. Gen. James Rainey and his wife Tracy Rainey. The student cadets and their senior advisors were recognized for winning the Raider National Championship in Molina, Ga., in November. Leavenworth Schools and Fort Leavenworth have an outstanding relationship and this was an unforgettable opportunity for the Raiders to have their accomplishments honored and receive warm hospitality by Lt. Gen. Rainey and Mrs. Rainey.

Good afternoon, from the Leavenworth School District,
Due to an increased number of anticipated absences associated with planned festivities celebrating the Kansas City Chiefs' Super Bowl win, there will be No School for students or staff on Wednesday, February 5, 2020.

This decision was not made lightly, and we are sensitive to the inconvenience this may cause for our families, hence the earlier than usual cancellation notification. The Horizon Kids program will be open for the day, and will operate with their regular daily schedule.

Pending any change in the celebration date, Leavenworth students will be back in session on Thursday, February 6, 2020.

Hi Livin Nutrition friends!! We have something great in store this month!!

We are partnering with Leavenworth Public Schools Education Foundation’s Inspire Group!!

What does this mean? It means that we will have a special shake called the “Inspire Your Health” Shake for the whole month!! So join us throughout January and Inspire Your Health while supporting the community!!

shared_text:
Leavenworth Public Schools Education Foundation
December 18, 2019 at 4:18 PM ·

The LV Education Foundation gained a new partner today!

Hugest thanks to First United Methodist Church of Leavenworth for a generous donation to the LV Education Foundation. The Rev. Dr. David York, Senior Pastor, and Wayne Parks, church member/LHS graduate/LV Education Foundation board of directors member, presented a check in the amount of $5,500 to Catey Edwards, Director of the LV Education Foundation (far left), and Holly Shehorn-Pittman, President of the LV Education Foundation (right center).

The excitement for what this means to Leavenworth students, through the Foundation's ability to support and "INSPIRE" teachers, was evident!

Many thanks to the First United Methodist Church for this most generous contribution as we work together to, "provide extraordinary educational opportunities for our Leavenworth students." This new partnership is just another piece of 20 years of giving!

The LV Education Foundation continues to grow its presence in the community, which allows for many new partnerships and “friends" of the Foundation. This month, we launch a new program called, “Become a Friend of the Foundation,” which features a new business connection each month and a special deal/product/sale, with a portion going back to the LV Education Foundation.

December's “Become a Friend of the Foundation” business - CANDLE QUEEN CANDLES! The featured item is a 16 oz “INSPIRE” candle, white with blue swirls and magic sprinkles in a pretty blue mason jar. The scent is the popular Grace, which is a heavenly grapefruit/amber, which will burn approximately 100 hours. The cost of each candle is $16, with $5 of each candle sale to go back to the LV Education Foundation!

Come get "inspired" and join us as we jump out into partnership with new businesses in our community - all for the good of our LV students!

November 20, 2019 at 10:25 AM ·

Last night at Warren Middle School = so much fun! It was the 7th Annual "Pioneers Spiking for a Cure - Pink Out Volleyball Game," where the 8th grade volleyball and football players took to the floor for some friendly competition....all for a great cause! All funds raised (a grand total of $316) will be donated to the KU Breast Cancer Survivorship Center! Thanks to Warren PIE for sponsoring this great tradition. And, a shout out to Brayden Kermode for singing the National Anthem, to the Warren cheerleaders (awesome spirit!), the Warren Pep Band, STUCO for running the amazing concession stand, and all fans! This event has become one of the most anticipated at the school...a celebration of many accomplishments on the field/court and in their middle school career. It's a great chance for memories as these students prepare to move on to the next chapter of their education. As always, GO Pioneers!

BTW, the GIRLS reigned victorious last night, bringing the win record to 5 girls/2 boys...

Leavenworth Senior High School
November 14, 2019 at 7:31 PM ·

LHS hosts an eastern region DECA competition with 13 schools and 450 students from the area. Students compete in career areas including business management, finance, hospitality, marketing, entrepreneurship, and personal financial literacy.

This certainly develops leaders and entrepreneurs, but more than that imparts lifelong skills such as critical thinking, problem solving, teamwork, and communication.

This event also serves as preparation for the state competition in March at KSU.

Thank you to the many community members who served as judges.

post_text: Happy Election Day! Ms. Schwalm's 2nd grade class at David Brewer Elementary School held their own election today. Students voted on which snack they wanted have for their class party: candy, chips or popcorn. To vote, students showed Ms. Schwalm their "ID cards" and then they entered the voting booth. After voting, they received a "I Voted Today!" sticker. Students were excited to give their input on what snacks they wanted and learned about voting, how it works, and why it is important.

Leavenworth High School Alumni Association
October 21, 2019 at 3:19 PM ·

The Leavenworth High School Class of 2009 recently hosted a ten-year reunion event that served not only as a celebration, but also a way to honor past and future graduates. The class used funds from the social event and several donations to put together a $1,000 scholarship for the LHS Alumni Association in memory of four classmates who had passed. The scholarship will be awarded to a 2020 graduate next spring.

Thanks for your time, memories, and connection to LHS, Class of 2009!

Once a Pioneer, Always a Pioneer!

Pictured:
Members of the Class of 2009 celebrating together during their reunion activities.
Class members present the check for the scholarship fund.

shared_text:
Leavenworth Senior High School
October 21, 2019 at 9:52 AM ·

As posted on the LHS Raider page -
Sharing an incredible story here...so proud of our RAIDERS! Go Pioneers!

What an honor it is to coach theses incredible young men and women. Our future looks strong and determined.

It’s been a long road back to Nationals. We have been training to win the title since November 4, 2018. The Raiders have put in 100s of hours of practice with first place parents supporting us the whole way.

The hard work has paid off with a 3 and 0 season heading into the big event.

We believe in this team. They have what it takes to be National Champions.

Keep your head up. Eye on the prize. It’s time to turn it up and make all of you champions. Be proud of yourself and your team. You can do this!!

11 days and a wake up until we are headed to Georgia to earn the title!!!

1SG
Coach Schwartz

Due to forecasted weather conditions for Friday evening, Leavenworth Senior High School's homecoming game vs. Turner will be moved up to a 5:00 p.m. Kick-Off on Friday, September 27.

The game will be preceded by the homecoming parade beginning at 2:00 p.m. beginning at 7th & Cherokee, proceeding north on 7th to Delaware, and continuing east on Delaware to Esplanade. North/South traffic on 4th Street will be blocked from 2:00 - 2:45 p.m.

Reminder that Friday is an early dismissal day - high school/middle school release at 11:30 a.m.; elementary schools dismiss at Noon.

Thank you in advance to City of Leavenworth – Government Leavenworth Police Department Leavenworth Main Street and all of our parents, boosters, and alumni for their support on behalf of our participating students and staff.

post_text: An amazing LHS senior...off to do great things in the future...
shared_text:
Leavenworth Senior High School
August 26, 2019 at 1:42 PM ·

What a cool accomplishment! Way to go, Ayden Bartlett!

PrepVolleyball.com is proud to present its Senior Aces, the top 250 volleyball recruits in the Class of 2020.

Passing serve is a critical skill in the college game. Bartlett makes it look effortless. An absolute gamer in the back row, Bartlett has the ability to make opposing servers think the court is shrinking. While muscling up big-time digs in clutch moments is nothing new to her, it is Bartlett’s ball control and passing that separate her from other back row players throughout the country. Bartlett has been playing a year above her grade for the past several years in club ball. The respect earned from her older teammates for her tireless work allows her to be a vocal leader who delivers strategic communication to her hitters during every play. An Honorable Mention All-State setter for her high school team, Bartlett has impacted the game in myriad ways over the years. Following in a long line of big time liberos, she is heading to the University of Louisville to make the rest of the ACC think twice before serving her way.

shared_text:
Leavenworth Senior High School
June 7, 2019 at 9:49 PM ·

Today the curtain closed on the 2019 LHS Summer Theatre Camp. Leavenworth and Lansing High School Theatre students worked as camp counselors this week guiding young campers through various theatre activities. Their hard work culminated in performances today on the big stage at the Leavenworth High School Performing Arts Center. The younger age group, consisting of Kindergarten through 4th grade, performed a show based on various childhood fairy tales. The older campers, grades 5-9, performed their rendition of "Dusty Boots," an original show written by two former Leavenworth High School theatre students. The campers worked hard, had a great time, and wowed the crowd!

Leavenworth Senior High School
May 23, 2019 at 8:23 AM ·

Congratulations to Michelle Denney, LHS junior to be senior, who was recognized by the Leavenworth County Human Service Council as an Honorable Mention for the Spirit of Humanitarianism Award. Michelle is a member of NHS, an excellent student, and is involved in a multitude of activities. She gives unselfishly of her time volunteering with St. Paul Lutheran Church and School, serving community meals, giving countless hours to LHS theatre productions, and many other acts of kindness. She is pretty much, just amazing. LHS is lucky to have her, and it is wonderful that she was recognized for her work.

Leavenworth Senior High School
May 17, 2019 at 5:28 PM ·

Important Graduation Update for Seniors and Pioneer Families ---
Due to space limitations for tomorrow's graduation at Leavenworth High School, please be advised that ONLY the BLUE tickets issued directly to you by your student, will grant entry for up to four guests inside the Main Gymnasium.

If you received a ticket through a secondary source, and are unsure if your ticket is a valid BLUE ticket, school staff will be available inside the south entrance foyer from 8:00 - 8:30 a.m. tomorrow. Note that doors will not open until 9:00 a.m. in advance of the 10:30 a.m. scheduled start to commencement exercises.

Additional seating to guests with Yellow Tickets will be available in the Small Gymnasium and Auditorium and an online link has been shared via email, on Facebook, and Twitter for family members to watch a live broadcast of the event.

We apologize for any inconvenience, and thank you for your patience as our district staff works hard to provide a safe, secure, and memorable event for you and your family.

post_text: During a morning assembly, Sara Davis, STEM teacher at David Brewer Elementary School, was recognized by the Air Force Association as their chapter teacher of the year, as well as the state teacher of the year! The Air Force Association worked with local school districts to identify educators working to further science, technology, engineering, and math opportunities for students. Special thanks to Lt. Col. Paul Theriot of the United States Air Force for personally presenting the award and talking with Brewer students about various career paths related to STEM. Congratulations, Mrs. Davis!
